President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Jeffrey R. Moreland for the position of Director on the Amtrak Board of Directors. Moreland has a background in law and government affairs, with previous roles at BNSF Railway Company and Santa Fe Railway. He also has experience working at the Securities and Exchange Commission. Moreland holds a B.S. from Georgetown University, a J.D. from Catholic University School of Law, and an MBA from the University of Chicago.